🌿 Texture & Feel:

Lightweight and creamy, it applies like a moisturizer — no stickiness, greasiness, or white cast, even on deeper skin tones. Perfect for daily wear and under makeup.

🌞 SPF Protection:

Offers broad-spectrum SPF 50+ PA++++ protection using chemical (organic) filters. Reliable for daily UV defense, though reapplication is key for extended sun exposure.

💧 Skin Benefits:

Infused with 30% rice extract and probiotics, it feels soothing and hydrating. Great for dry to combo skin — and it won’t clog pores, so acne-prone skin can enjoy it too.

🧴 Finish:

Leaves a natural, radiant finish — not matte, but not shiny either. Ideal for a “glass skin” look without feeling oily.

If you’re someone who hates the sticky, heavy feeling most sunscreens leave behind — this one might just be your new BFF.

What I personally love:🤌
• The texture is super light and watery — it literally feels like I’m applying a serum or lightweight moisturizer.
• It leaves my skin dewy, fresh, and hydrated — perfect for days when I want a no-makeup, healthy glow.
• No white cast at all (huge plus!) and it blends into my skin so effortlessly.
• Works beautifully under my makeup — no pilling, no weird patchiness.

Skin feel after application?💗
Moisturized, calm, and glowy — not greasy. And I’ve got combination skin, so I appreciate that it hydrates my dry areas while not making my T-zone oily.

Overall Verdict:🌻
This sunscreen feels more like skincare. It protects, hydrates, and gives a glow that looks like I’ve just done a full skincare routine.
Would I repurchase? Definitely.
It’s made sunscreen feel less like a chore and more like a treat.

I’ve been using The 6 Peptide Skin Booster Serum for a while now, and honestly — it’s a quiet skincare hero.

From the first application, I loved the watery texture — it’s super lightweight, absorbs quickly, and doesn’t leave any sticky or greasy feel. It sinks right in and makes your skin feel fresh, not heavy.

After consistent use, here’s what I noticed:
	•	My skin feels smoother and more plump. There’s a subtle bounce to it that wasn’t there before.
	•	It gives a healthy glow — not oily or shiny, just a nice dewy radiance.
	•	No irritation at all, which is a big win for my sensitive skin. It’s fragrance-free and really gentle.
	•	It works beautifully under makeup and layers well with other products — no pilling or weird reactions.

The peptides in this serum are what make it special — they help with skin repair, firmness, and elasticity over time. So while it doesn’t give “instant results,” it really nourishes your skin and supports long-term health.

Would I repurchase? Yes.
Would I recommend it? Absolutely — especially if you’re into lightweight, no-fuss skincare that actually works

I’ve been using the Aromatica Aloe Vera Gel for a few weeks now, and honestly, it’s become a go-to in my skincare routine. It contains 95% organic aloe vera, which is amazing for calming irritated or sensitive skin. What really stood out to me is the texture—lightweight, non-sticky, and fast-absorbing. Unlike some gels that leave a tacky feeling, this one feels refreshing and super clean on the skin.

I mainly use it as a soothing gel after sun exposure, and it instantly cools my skin down. I’ve also tried it as a light moisturizer on hot or humid days, and it gives just the right amount of hydration without clogging pores. It works great as an after-shave gel too—no stinging, just calm, soft skin.

Another plus: it’s fragrance-free, vegan, and cruelty-free, which makes it feel even better to use. I also appreciate that it comes in a huge pump bottle, so it lasts a long time and is easy to apply.

If you’re dealing with redness, irritation, or just need a simple, multi-use hydrating product—this is a great one to try. It’s gentle enough for sensitive skin, and versatile enough to use in many ways.

Would I repurchase? Yes, definitely. It’s a solid, affordable product that actually delivers what it promises.
